# R2DB Postgres with datatype Point

I found this interesting behavior recently, and wanted to create a small repo to share it quickly.

Basically, whenever we have entities in Postgres with the [`Point` datatype](https://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.4/datatype-geometric.html), we can fetch existing values using a simple R2dbcCrudRepository, but we can never insert nor update values, [getting errors described below](#error-message):


### How to use this repo to test it out:

I must admit I couldn't setup testcontainers in the time I alloted myself to prepare this demo, so the setup is a bit dumb. Bear with me:
You can run the tests defined in this repo by using:
```
$ make test
```
In detail: 
- I provided a `docker-compose.yaml` file to start a postgres image with postgres/postgres.
- Running the `make test` command above will start the container and run the gradle tests
- If you wanna test in the IDE, run first `make run-db` to start the DB.

The tests will apply a Flyway migration defining a simple table named `pointy_table` containing the `location` attribute that uses the `Point` datatype, and populate it with data.

The tests at [`TestPointHandling`](src/test/kotlin/com/xunfos/r2dbpointissue/point/TestPointHandling.kt) will try to load data and insert data

- The load tests are successful, the insert tests fail with the error mentioned below.
